               <note>
                  <date type="foundation" notBefore="1400" notAfter="1500">1400-1500</date>
                  <desc type="foundation">Local tradition tells that the rock-hewn church is ancient foundation; it was re-established in the time of King Yosṭos (r. 1711-16) and King Yoḥannǝs IV (r. 1872-89).</desc>
                  <ab type="history">Gädam. The monastic community declined, only a few monks reside at the church.  &#xD;
</ab>
                  <ab type="description">9 Mss. photographed: <ref type="mss" corresp="ESbhm001">BHM-001</ref> “Four Gospels”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESbhm002">BHM-002</ref> “Miracles of Mary”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESbhm003">BHM-003</ref> “Homiliany for the feasts of St. Michael; Miracles of Michael f. 59R; Homily of the 24 Heavenly Priests”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESbhm004">BHM-004</ref> “Missal”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESbhm005">BHM-005</ref> “Homily of Mary”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESbhm006">BHM-006</ref> “Synaxarium (second part)”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESbhm007">BHM-007</ref> “Synaxarium (The first half of the year)”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESbhm008">BHM-008</ref> “Collection of Images ”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESbhm009">BHM-009</ref> “Book of the Baptismal Rite”.</ab>
